article.headline: Bowling Green routs Presbyterian 67-45
article.story: CANCUN, Mexico -- Anthony Henderson scored 17 points in a rout as Bowling Green beat Presbyterian 67-45 in the Cancun Challenge on Tuesday. Bowling Green was up big at halftime, 33-19, as the Falcons defense held Presbyterian to just five field goals in the first 20 minutes. Presbyterian cut it to 41-33 with less than 15 minutes left, but Bowling Green built its lead to 19 point (56-37) with just under 8 minutes left. Cameron Black added 12 points, 14 rebounds and Jehvon Clark added 10 point and passed out nine assists for Bowling Green (2-3). The Falcons made 56.9 of its 51 shots. Presbyterian (1-6) shot just 30.6 percent from the field. Jordan Downing had 14 points, on 5-of-16 shooting, and William Truss made just 4 of 13, finishing with 12 points.
